        "created_at": "2024-03-19T16:33:57.848Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi all!<br>\nThe latest Operator release 1.35 will no longer support stateful processGroups to be created without PVCs.<br>\nThis change was motivated when investigating some logic which allowed stateful processes to not have PVCs when a default spec was specified that did not have a volume or storage resource requests.  We felt that it was more likely for someone to do this by accident than on purpose, and that stateful processes with no PVCs would not work in either case.<br>\nThe code changes can be viewed in this <a href=\"https://github.com/FoundationDB/fdb-kubernetes-operator/pull/1965\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">PR here</a>.<br>\nPlease let us know here and/or file issues if this change is problematic for your use cases.<br>\nThanks!</p>",
